Current comprehensive diagnosis of pancreatobiliary cancer complicated by jaundice syndrome. The study was undertaken to enhance the efficiency of diagnosis of pancreatobiliary cancer complicated by jaundice by using the potentialities of currently available instrumental studies at most. The data of examination of 256 patients with this disease are presented. Based on diagnostic findings, the authors have constructed a diagnostic model of precision recognition of cancer of the extrahepatic bile ducts, pancreatic head, Vater's papilla.